      "description": "Available for the discerning enthusiast is a mechanically robust E46 M3, powered by the high-strung S54B32 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit features double VANOS variable valve timing and individual throttle bodies, providing an exceptionally responsive torque curve and an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox and a limited-slip M Variable Differential Lock. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including reinforcement of the rear subframe floor and rod bearing replacement. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from refreshed suspension bushings and precise steering rack feedback. This example offers a balanced performance profile, retaining its factory-spec handling characteristics and mechanical integrity for a pure analog driving experience.",
